[These cases could be caused by a variety of pathogens. Laboratory confirmation (or exclusion) is necessary to determine if these cases are due to Nipah virus infection or something else. In the past, Nipah virus infection has been confirmed as the cause of 5 previously undiagnosed cases of illness in the Nadia district of West Bengal. Should Nipah virus infection be confirmed, source of the current outbreak and the involvement of bats, pigs, and domestic cats and dogs have still to be established. Giant fruit bats (genus _Pteropus_) are reservoirs of Nipah virus in Bangladesh and Malaysia, and are likely to be in India as well. Further laboratory information is awaited. - Mod.TY

